      <text>Relating probability values to real-life situations</text>
    </name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<p>Consider {@situation_text@}. Which of the following best represents the probability of this event?</p>

<p>[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]] [[feedback:prt1]]</p>]]></text>
    </questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
      <text><![CDATA[<h3>Worked Solution</h3>

<p>A probability of <strong>0</strong> represents an impossible event.</p>
<p>A probability of <strong>1</strong> represents a certain event.</p>
<p>A probability between <strong>0 and 1</strong> represents an uncertain event.</p>

<p>The correct probability value for this situation is <strong>{@correct_prob@}</strong>.</p>]]></text>
    </generalfeedback>
